<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-07-31T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-07-31T18:00:00-05:00" n="646" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d646">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 862.85/104</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in Siam</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_AFD1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Arnold</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-07-31T18:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 31, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>American International Corporation has proposed to Siamese
                                Government, through Pitkin, purchase nine recently seized German
                                steamers. Inform Siamese Government, corporation trusts its proposal
                                will be favorably received. You are instructed to take such steps as
                                you may find possible to expedite the transaction.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>